# Workflow

> **⛔ PC FROZEN (mobile phase)** — PC base CSS·`main`/`div` 레이아웃·`md:*` **수정 금지**. 모바일은 `mobile/*.css`만. → [09-pc-frozen-mobile-only.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/09-pc-frozen-mobile-only.mdc)

- Smallest correct diff; match existing style in the touched folder
- **Implement only what the user asked for in the current message.** Do not add, remove, or refactor unrelated behavior (mobile CSS/JSX, pagination, animation, docs, tests, rule files) unless explicitly requested.
- If a fix suggests a related improvement, mention it briefly and wait for approval — do not implement proactively.
- After backend edits: `cd server && npm test` when tests exist
- After frontend edits: note if `cd front && npm start` should be run manually
- Do not create git commits unless the user asks
- Do not add dependencies without stating why; prefer stdlib and existing stack
- Explain breaking changes briefly when API or folder layout shifts

Structure changes must update [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) and the relevant `sub.md` in the same task (`sub.md` does not auto-sync).

When adding routes, pages, or top-level folders, update the matching `sub.md` before finishing.
